# Notice of Motion

## What this document is
A Notice of Motion is a formal document used to ask the court to make a decision or take a specific action in a case.

## Why this document exists
It informs the other parties and the court about what you are asking the court to do and the reasons for your request.

## How to fill it out
1. Write the court file number and court location.
2. State the date and time when the motion will be heard.
3. Clearly explain what order or decision you are asking the court to make.
4. Include a brief explanation of why you are making this request.

## Important note
A Notice of Motion must be served to the other parties involved in the case and filed with the court in advance of the hearing date.
